text: More people have died of an opioid overdose in North Carolina in recent years than have died of COVID.
Significantly more people died of Covid-19 in two months than died of overdoses all of last year or the year before.
More people, aged 18-45, died of Fentanyl overdoses in 2020 than covid, car accidents, cancer, + suicide combined.
More people died from suicide than from Covid-19 in August.
San Francisco had twice as many drug overdose deaths as COVID deaths last year.
More people died of suicide in 2020 than died of COVID-19.
